Those wares may be sold. And why, then, should they not be sold? An honorable and

fair price for them can now be received, and why, then, should they not be retailed at the present time? Philosophers teach that a fair 220 price is not a fixed point, but may vary somewhat. Do I say, “ the philosophers ”? All the jurists and all theologians hold the same view.
